	abstract = {* Cuticle thickness of leaves varies {\textgreater} 100 times across species, yet its dry mass cost and ecological benefits are poorly understood. It has been repeatedly demonstrated that thicker cuticle is not superior as a water barrier, implying that other functions must be important.

